      "id": "cluster_005",
      "name": "The Agentic Org (POV / Narrative Pillar)",
      "description": "Point-of-view pillar inspired by Salesforce's agentic-engineering trilogy (getting-engineers-to-use-ai, agentic-enterprise-design-principles, how-engineering-became-agentic). Three STANDALONE posts — deliberately NOT a bound 'Part 1 of 3' series; each ranks on its own intent and ships independently — grounded in Dakota's real, fully ANONYMIZED work leading a consultancy's agentic transformation. (1) Adoption: distribution beats capability — a central Claude Code marketplace + catalog that got a non-technical org using AI via a no-terminal Claude.ai MCP-connector path + role playbooks. (2) Design principles: an ENFORCED governance spine (15-module AI governance framework + NIST conformance, artifact taxonomy, least privilege, CI validator) — principles in code, not slides. (3) Transformation/frontier: the arc from a personal autonomous setup -> an org-wide catalog -> a governed declarative agent fleet. This is the narrative layer ABOVE the four technical clusters: it explains WHY they exist and links DOWN into them. Hard constraints: anonymize the org entirely (no company name, role codes, or client data); the unreleased Plugin Factory beta stays OUT of all three posts. Reinforces (does not cannibalize) cluster_002 — see content_gaps gap_004. Closes gap_004.",
